# Testing Conventions

Aligns with AGENTS.md testing guidelines + adds AskQuestion-driven test workflow.

## Core Rules

- Framework: Vitest with V8 coverage (70% threshold for lines/branches/functions/statements)
- Test files: colocated `*.test.ts`, e2e in `*.e2e.test.ts`
- Run: `pnpm test` before pushing when touching logic
- Live tests: `CLAWDBOT_LIVE_TEST=1 pnpm test:live` or `LIVE=1 pnpm test:live`

## After Writing Code

When implementation is done and tests are relevant, proactively suggest testing:

```
AskQuestion({
  title: "Implementation Done - Testing",
  questions: [
    {
      id: "test-action",
      prompt: "Code changes complete. How should we handle testing?",
      options: [
        { id: "run-related", label: "Run tests related to changed files" },
        { id: "run-all", label: "Run full test suite (pnpm test)" },
        { id: "write-tests", label: "Write/update tests for the new code" },
        { id: "coverage", label: "Check coverage (pnpm test:coverage)" },
        { id: "skip", label: "Skip testing for now" },
        { id: "custom", label: "Other" }
      ]
    }
  ]
})
```

## After Test Failures

When tests fail, present actionable options:

```
AskQuestion({
  title: "Test Failures Detected",
  questions: [
    {
      id: "fix-strategy",
      prompt: "Tests failed. How should I proceed?",
      options: [
        { id: "auto-fix", label: "Auto-fix the failures (recommended for obvious fixes)" },
        { id: "show-errors", label: "Show me the full error details first" },
        { id: "revert", label: "Revert changes and try a different approach" },
        { id: "skip", label: "Skip failing tests and continue" },
        { id: "custom", label: "Other strategy" }
      ]
    }
  ]
})
```

## Test Writing Patterns

When writing tests for openclaw:
- Use `describe/it` blocks with clear descriptions
- Mock external dependencies (channels, APIs, file system)
- Test both happy path and edge cases
- For CLI commands: test flag parsing, output formatting, error handling
- For channels: test message routing, allowlists, pairing
- For gateway: test lifecycle, health checks, connection management

## Proactive Test Suggestions

When reading code that lacks tests, flag it in AskQuestion options:
- "I noticed [file] has no test coverage - want me to add tests?"
- "The [function] handles auth but has no edge case tests - should I add them?"
- "This new code path isn't covered by existing tests - want me to scaffold a test file?"
